==English==

===Etymology 1===
Old English ''[[fann]]'', from the Latin ''[[vannus]]'', "fan for winnowing grain".

====Noun====
'''fan''' (''plural:'' [[fans]])
# A [[hand-held]] device consisting of [[concertina]]ed material, or slats of material, gathered together at one end, that may be opened out into the shape of a [[sector]] of a circle and waved back and forth in order to move air towards oneself and cool oneself.
#An electrical device for moving air, used for cooling people, machinery, etc.
#Anything resembling a hand-held fan in shape, e.g., a [[peacock]]'s [[tail]].

